I don't see why people complain, the sound is a little bit funny but it doesn't bother the enjoyment of the film at all. This copy has awesome video, and the audio is in sync and you can hear everything they say. The only thing I noticed was it seemed to cut in and out a few times in the movie, but not in action parts only during parts where nobody was even talking. It also seemed like there was some kind of noise in the background in the beginning, like someone was walking around the house, but it didn't seem to fit in. Like I said though, those things are pretty trivial so if you want to watch the movie this is probably your better option. & for those of you saying thanks but no thanks, I'll wait for a better copy... what is the point? It is not only a waste of your time to make a stupid comment like that but it is a waste of others time as well if people want to know ratings of the film. Nobody cares if you want to wait for a better copy, if you do go to er, but don't whine about a copy you haven't seen just based on the info or if you prefer watching high quality blueray films or something.. try waiting until they come out in stores and watch it then instead of whining and making the decent copies look bad to others who are simply appreciative of a copy like this.
